{{!-- Shared sidebar character-sheet header content. Renders inside the
     wh40k-sidebar PARTS container; per-system header files wrap this in
     a flex column and append any system-specific extras after it.

     Order: actor-identity (name input above portrait, with origin-builder
     overlay) → divination display (italic, when set).

     Works for both PC and NPC actors via the universal `actor.name`,
     `originPathComplete`, and `system.originPath.divination` context.
     Game-specific origin-path stage UI belongs in the relevant child header
     template, not in this shared parent partial. --}}

{{> systems/wh40k-rpg/templates/actor/partial/actor-identity.hbs withOriginBuilder=true}}

{{!-- Divination line (#389). When the divination step carries a compendium
     reference (system.originPath.divinationUuid — the structured bonus grant
     from #316), render the omen quote as a clickable link that opens the
     compendium entry via the shared `openUuid` action. Falls back to plain
     text when no UUID is stored (legacy PCs / NPCs without a divination item).
     Per-system safe: the UUID resolves against the actor's own game system. --}}
{{#if system.originPath.divination}}
<p class="tw-italic tw-opacity-60 tw-m-0 tw-text-center tw-text-xs tw-leading-snug tw-text-[var(--wh40k-text-muted)]">{{#if system.originPath.divinationUuid}}<a data-action="openUuid" data-uuid="{{system.originPath.divinationUuid}}" role="button" tabindex="0" class="tw-text-inherit tw-italic tw-underline tw-decoration-dotted tw-cursor-pointer hover:tw-opacity-100" data-tooltip="{{localize 'WH40K.OriginPath.OpenDivinationTooltip'}}" aria-label="{{localize 'WH40K.OriginPath.OpenDivinationTooltip'}}">{{system.originPath.divination}}</a>{{else}}{{system.originPath.divination}}{{/if}}</p>
{{/if}}
